Something useful to know is CONDITION TERNARY OPERATOR, you can read up on MDN web docs. It is good for substituting an if statement with for a less verbose ternary operator, this applies for javascript and php(some other languages may also support it).

<?php 
    $isMale = true;
    echo ($isMale ? "You are male" : "You are not male");
?>

This is the same as....

<?php
    $isMale = true;
    if($isMale) {
        echo "You are male";
    } else {
